ETCopyData:compare.description: Checks the source and destination org for any differences in the sObject's metadata, this helps determine what data can be properly exported/imported.

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

ETCopyData:delete.description: Deletes data from destination org, preparing for the new data that will be uploaded. Note: Deleting optionally happens before loading, but if there are some errors this operation can be retired by itself.

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

ETCopyData:export.description: Exports the data from the source org, and saves it in the destination folder so that it can be imported at a later time.

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

ETCopyData:full.description: Performs all the steps, including comparing schemas, exporting data from the source, optionally deleting data from the destination, and importing the data to the destination org. This may help you when setting up a new process

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

ETCopyData:import.description: Imports data into destination org, you can control if the data in the destination sObjects should be removed before loading a new data set. The data load happens in a specific order (children first, parents last) which has been determined by checking the schema in the destination org.

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation
